modules.description: Checks whether a specified substring consists entirely of zero bytes. Works directly with string inputs and integer length parameters. Useful for validating null-terminated fields in binary data formats or ensuring memory buffers are initialized to zero.

Performs efficient validation of zero-filled substrings in strings using direct memory inspection. Accepts a string and length, returning true if all bytes in the specified range are zero. Ideal for checking null-terminated fields in binary protocols or confirming zero-initialized memory buffers.
